Dysentery, severe - Russia (Murmansk) 980103191343
Dysentery, severe - Russia (Murmansk) (03) 980116230258
Shigellosis - Russia (Udmurtia) 980812200053
Shigellosis - Russia (Volgograd) 980815185758
Date: 12 May 2000
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: ITAR/TASS News Agency, 11 May 2000 [edited

Cheboksary and Novocheboksarsk in Chuvashia report an increasing number of
intestinal infection cases caused by low-quality dairy products made in
Cheboksary. In the city, a total of 1174 people (including 657 children)
have already fallen [ill, with 560 people hospitalised for dysentery.
There are 418 similar cases including 271 among children in
Novocheboksarsk. The figure for the Cheboksary region is 70 cases with
children accounting for more than half of them.
Specialists from federal epidemiologic services have been sent to the
region to render aid.
--
